quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  82,1,When the heaven will cleft asunder
  82,2,and when the stars will scatter
  82,3,and when the oceans are burst out
  82,4,and when the graves will be turned upside down (bring out their contents)
  82,5,every person will know what he has sent forward and what left behind
  82,6,"O people! What has made you careless about your Lord, the Generous"
  82,7,"who created you, fashioned you perfectly, gave you due proportion"
  82,8,and put you together in whatever form He willed
  82,9,Nay! But you deny the Day of Judgment
  82,10,"But surely, (angels have been appointed to watch) over you"
  82,11,(who are) honorable writers
  82,12,they know all of what you do
  82,13,"Surely, (on that Day) the righteous will be in delight (Paradise)"
  82,14,"and surely, the wicked (evil-doers) will be in the fire (hell)"
  82,15,and they will burn in it on the Day of recompense
  82,16,and they will not be able to escape from it
  82,17,And what will make you know what the Day of the recompense is
  82,18,"Again, what will make you know what the Day of recompense is"
  82,19,"(It will be) the Day when no one will have the power to do anything for another: on that Day, the decision will be entirely with Allah"
  83,1,Woe to those who give less in measure and weight (defraud)
  83,2,"those who, when they receive by measure from people, demand full measure"
  83,3,"but when they give by measure or give by weight to others, they give less than due"
